ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 6th day of May, 2015, the Application to File Under Seal is GRANTED, and the Application for Extraordinary Relief is DENIED, WITHOUT PREJUDICE to Petitioner’s challenges pending in the Superior Court. See Commonwealth v. Schultz, 280 MDA 2015; Commonwealth v. Schultz, 14 MDM 2015.
Justice STEVENS joins the Order in all respects, except that he would deny the application to file under seal.
